# Aider Environment Variables (LDDE-ZeroTouch)
# For pure local Ollama usage you usually need NOTHING in here.
# Only populate keys if you deliberately want to use a cloud model as fallback or for /Mode review etc.

# Local Ollama is the default (see .aider.conf.yml + Start-Aider.ps1 -Mode local)
# ollama must be running on http://127.0.0.1:11434

# Optional cloud fallbacks only
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Tip: Keep this file minimal. The real power is in the local instructions + custom commands
# that were built from the 4 research files in local first/
